com.ptc.core.meta.container.common

Interface ConstraintSummary

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AttributeTypeSummary
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultAttributeTypeSummary

    public interface ConstraintSummary
    Summarizes the constraint information for an attribute. The constraint summary information can vary depending on the OperationIdentifier used when retrieving the constraints. That each constraint summary is specific to the operation it was retrieved for. Many constraints are only enforced for create/update operations. As a result many of these methods will return different results for the same attribute when the constraint summary is retrieved for a create operation vs. a display operation.
    See Also:


    Supported API: true

    Extendable: false

        DataSet getLegalValueSet()
        Key for the set of legal values for the attribute. A null value for this key signifies that (virtually) any value is legal. An empty set signifies that no values are legal. A populated set signifies the legal values.
